About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.title: Ek Date Aisi Bhi | Take A Break
snippet.description:
In Ek Date Aisi Bhi, join three friends as they set out on what they think will be the perfect romantic dates‚Ä¶ only for everything to go hilariously wrong! üò¨üíî
From awkward silences and weird restaurant choices to unexpected ex-encounters and disastrous conversations, each date turns into a comedy of errors. But just when all hope seems lost, a surprising twist brings unexpected connections and a dash of real love into the mix.
Full of laughs, relatable moments, and a sweet message, this sketch proves that sometimes, even the worst dates can lead to the best stories.‚ù§Ô∏è

snippet.description:
#goodbadugly #ajith #adhikravichandran #director #interview 

Director Adhik Ravichandar's Exclusive Interview about Good Bad Ugly with Sudharshan Gandhi

In this conversation, Adhik Ravichandar discusses the success of Mark Antony and takes us through the journey of Good Bad Ugly ‚Äî from ideation to post-production. He shares insights into the casting process, the film's technical team, and how he aimed to create a visual treat for Ajith's fans. Adhik also opens up about his experience of directing Ajith as a fan, as well as the memorable days spent shooting with him. Additionally, he speaks about his father and father-in-law, actor Prabhu, and shares his thoughts on Ajith's deep connection with his fans and Ajith‚Äôs Padma Bhushan award.

Director Adhik Ravichandar's Exclusive Interview about Good Bad Ugly with Sudharshan Gandhi

In this conversation, Adhik Ravichandar discusses the success of Mark Antony and takes us through the journey of Good Bad Ugly ‚Äî from ideation to post-production. He shares insights into the casting process, the film's technical team, and how he aimed to create a visual treat for Ajith's fans. Adhik also opens up about his experience of directing Ajith as a fan, as well as the memorable days spent shooting with him. Additionally, he speaks about his father and father-in-law, actor Prabhu, and shares his thoughts on Ajith's deep connection with his fans and Ajith‚Äôs Padma Bhushan award.

snippet.description:
Gokuldham Society | Gada Electronics | Bonus | Financial Year

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. Are you ready for the challenge? 

 Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  #GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame


Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada

snippet.description:
Dhyan Sreenivasan Crashes Annie‚Äôs Kitchen! üòÇüçç Vishu Special with a Sweet Twist!

This Vishu, Annie's Kitchen is filled with laughter, surprises, and sweet moments as the charming Dhyan Sreenivasan joins Annie for a festive feast! üéâ

Annie starts off the celebration by preparing a special Vishu Pradhaman, a rich and delicious payasam that sets the mood just right. But the real surprise? Dhyan walks in as a guest and stuns Annie with his unexpected visit! üò≤üíõ

As Annie plans to treat Dhyan with a grand Vishu Sadya, she suddenly realizes she forgot to make kichadi ‚Äì specifically the pineapple version she had in mind. That‚Äôs when Dhyan steps in with full spirit, offering to help her in the kitchen! üççüë®‚Äçüç≥

Get ready for a cooking session packed with witty puns, playful banter, and heartwarming conversations as Annie and Dhyan team up to whip up the perfect Pineapple Kichadi. Along the way, Dhyan opens up about his latest projects, personal updates, and of course, adds his signature humor to every moment.

Don‚Äôt miss this fun-filled, flavor-packed Vishu Special Episode of Annie‚Äôs Kitchen! üåº‚ú®

"Annie's Kitchen" is a unique and exciting cookery-cum-chat show, airing every Friday at 8 PM on Amrita TV. In its second season, this delightful program is hosted by the multi-talented and charming Annie Shaji Kailas, a well-known actress in the Indian film industry. Join Annie as she whips up delicious and mouth-watering dishes in the kitchen, showcasing her culinary skills while inviting celebrity guests from the world of entertainment to join her.

                The show is divided into two engaging segments. In the first segment, watch as Annie demonstrates how to prepare a special dish, adding her personal touch and sharing handy cooking tips that will leave you craving more. In the second segment, the real fun begins! Annie sits down for a lively and entertaining chat with her celebrity guests, asking them humorous, intriguing  questions that reveal fascinating stories from their lives and careers.

                                         Annie, who is married to renowned filmmaker Shaji Kailas, brings a perfect blend of warmth and wit to every episode. Together, they have become a beloved couple in the industry, and Annie‚Äôs playful charm and insightful interviews make "Annie's Kitchen" a must-watch for viewers of all ages.

snippet.title: Superman | Sneak Peek
snippet.description:
Krypto, take us home. #Superman - Only in Theaters July 11

‚ÄúSuperman,‚Äù DC Studios‚Äô first feature film to hit the big screen, is set to soar into theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures.  In his signature style, James Gunn takes on the original superhero in the newly imagined DC universe with a singular blend of epic action, humor and heart, delivering a Superman who‚Äôs driven by compassion and an inherent belief in the goodness of humankind.

DC Studios heads Peter Safran and Gunn are producing the film, which Gunn directs from his own screenplay, based on characters from DC, Superman created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.

The film stars David Corenswet (‚ÄúTwisters,‚Äù ‚ÄúHollywood‚Äù) in the dual role of Superman/Clark Kent, Rachel Brosnahan (‚ÄúThe Marvelous Mrs. Maisel‚Äù) as Lois Lane and Nicholas Hoult (the ‚ÄúX-Men‚Äù movies, ‚ÄúJuror #2‚Äù) as Lex Luthor.  The film also stars Edi Gathegi (‚ÄúFor All Mankind‚Äù), Anthony Carrigan (‚ÄúBarry,‚Äù ‚ÄúGotham‚Äù), Nathan Fillion (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Suicide Squad‚Äù), Isabela Merced (‚ÄúAlien Romulus‚Äù), Skyler Gisondo (‚ÄúLicorice Pizza,‚Äù ‚ÄúBooksmart‚Äù), Sara Sampaio (‚ÄúAt Midnight‚Äù), Mar√≠a Gabriela de Far√≠a (‚ÄúThe Moodys‚Äù), Wendell Pierce (‚ÄúSelma,‚Äù ‚ÄúTom Clancy‚Äôs Jack Ryan‚Äù), Alan Tudyk (‚ÄúAndor‚Äù), Pruitt Taylor Vince (‚ÄúBird Box‚Äù) and Neva Howell (‚ÄúGreedy People‚Äù).

‚ÄúSuperman‚Äù is executive produced by Nikolas Korda, Chantal Nong Vo and Lars Winther.  Behind the camera, Gunn is joined by frequent collaborators, including director of photography Henry Braham, production designer Beth Mickle, costume designer Judianna Makovsky and composer John Murphy, along with editors William Hoy (‚ÄúThe Batman‚Äù), Jason Ballantine (the ‚ÄúIT‚Äù films, ‚ÄúThe Flash‚Äù) and Craig Alpert (‚ÄúDeadpool 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlue Beetle‚Äù).

‚ÄúSuperman‚Äù will be in theaters and IMAX nationwide on July 11, 2025, and internationally beginning 9 July 2025, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures.

snippet.title: FilterCopy | Reality of a NEET Aspirant | Ft. Tanya Sharma, Ruma Mondal
snippet.description:
Being a NEET aspirant in India? It‚Äôs not just about books and mock tests‚Äîit's a whole emotional rollercoaster filled with anxiety, last-minute revision, relatives asking the wrong questions, and friends who mean well but say the weirdest things. üò©üìö

In this hilarious and painfully relatable FilterCopy sketch, we dive into the reality of a NEET student‚Äôs life‚Äîthe pressure, the panic, and of course, the people who keep saying things like:
üëâ ‚ÄúBeta, NEET nikaalna toh easy hai na?‚Äù
üëâ ‚ÄúArey Sharma ji ka beta bhi kar raha hai!‚Äù
üëâ ‚ÄúTumhe toh doctor banne ka passion hai na?‚Äù üòê

From group studies that turn into therapy sessions to panic before results day, this one‚Äôs for all the NEET warriors out there fighting their way through syllabus, stress, and society. üò≠‚úä

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant.
